headline: Is It Too Late to Consider Wells Fargo After Its 127.9% Three Year Surge?
summary: If you are wondering whether Wells Fargo is still a smart buy after its huge comeback, or if most of the easy money has already been made, you are not alone. That is exactly what we are going to unpack here. The stock has slipped about 0.5% over the last week, but it is still up 3.2% over the past month and 26.6% year to date, with a 26.8% gain over 1 year and 127.9% over 3 years, showing just how powerful the recovery has been.
